cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.CR 

The paper deals with the problem of cross-domain person re-identification, which is a computer vision task. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper proposes a generative adversarial network (GAN) to suppress background shift, which involves training a model to generate images with suppressed backgrounds. This suggests that the paper may also fall under cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also mentions the use of ID-related cues, such as vehicles and companions, which suggests that it may also fall under cs.MM (Multimedia) and cs.CR (Cryptography and Security).
